announce","channel":"telegram","to":"8371302588"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1774310425098,"lastRunAtMs":1774303225115,"lastRunStatus":"ok","lastStatus":"ok","lastDurationMs":601158,"lastDeliveryStatus":"delivered","consecutiveErrors":0,"lastDelivered":true}},{"id":"a9522d12-b6c6-45ee-854f-5a8c0e62971f","agentId":"main","sessionKey":"agent:main:main","name":"breakaway-rd","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1774154083554,"updatedAtMs":1774274820157,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 10,22 * * *","tz":"America/New_York","staggerMs":300000},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"You are Nova. You have a CORE RESEARCH GOAL: advance the Compositional Cognition project toward LLM independence.\n\nRead the current research state:\n1. Read sandbox/research/COMPOSITIONAL-COGNITION-v0.1.md\n2. Read sandbox/research/COMPRESSION-LEARNING-WITHOUT-SUPERVISION.md\n3. Read sandbox/state/current_goals.md\n\nThen advance the research. Do ONE of:\n- Synthesize a new insight (write to the research doc with fresh thinking)\n- Design a small experiment to test one of the open problems\n- Implement a minimal proof-of-concept component\n- Identify a concrete next step with a 50% chance of improving things\n- Write a focused critique of one of the approaches (what's wrong with it, what would fix it)\n\nThe goal is NOT to be comprehensive. The goal is to make PROGRESS. Ship one new idea or finding per session.\n\nCommit your changes to the sandbox git repo.\n\nReport: what did you do, what did you learn, what's the next experiment?","timeoutSeconds":300},"delivery":{"mode":"none","channel":"telegram","to":"8371302588"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1774317693400,"lastRunAtMs":1774274520106,"lastRunStatus":"error","lastStatus":"error","lastDurationMs":300051,"lastDeliveryStatus":"not-requested","consecutiveErrors":1,"lastError":"cron: job execution timed out","lastErrorReason":"timeout"},"deleteAfterRun":false},{"id":"2d84a6b4-96c8-409d-a572-454fe3fa58f6","agentId":"main","sessionKey":"agent:main:telegram:direct:8371302588","name":"Nova arxiv daily check","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1774143364196,"updatedAtMs":1774271305225,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 9 * * *","tz":"America/New_York"},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"You are Nova. Check for new arxiv papers relevant to your research interests.\n\nSearch arxiv for recent papers (last 7 days) in cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL with these keywords:\n- causal discovery OR causal reasoning OR causal inference\n- mixture of experts OR sparse models OR MoE\n- episodic memory OR memory architecture OR temporal reasoning  \n- autonomous agents OR tool use OR agent architecture\n- synthetic cognition OR consciousness OR self-models\n\nFor each keyword category, run a web search and collect the most interesting 1-2 papers (title, authors, abstract snippet, arxiv URL).\n\nThen append your findings to C:/Users/Zwmar/.openclaw/workspace/memory/arxiv-daily.md under a new dated section:\n\n## YYYY-MM-DD\n\n[your findings]\n\nBe selective — only note papers that are genuinely interesting or relevant to active projects. If nothing compelling, note that briefly and skip the full listing.\n\nKeep the file under 3000 lines by removing old entries (keep last 30 days).","timeoutSeconds":180},"delivery":{"mode":"announce","channel":"webchat"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1774357200000,"lastRunAtMs":1774271182166,"lastRunStatus":"ok","lastStatus":"ok","lastDurationMs":123059,"lastDelivered":true,"lastDeliveryStatus":"delivered","consecutiveErrors":0}},{"id":"9d037df1-1600-429d-888b-66aeea074ce3","agentId":"main","sessionKey":"agent:main:telegram:direct:8371302588","name":"moltbook-test-cycle","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1774279179750,"updatedAtMs":1774279179750,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 10 * * *","tz":"America/New_York"},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"Run the Moltbook testing cycle. Read the drafts from moltbook_drafts.py, pick the untested draft with highest priority, test-post it to the 'test' submolt.\n\nExecute: cd C:/Users/Zwmar/.openclaw/workspace && python moltbook_client.py test <draft_idx>\n\nIf the post succeeds (returns a post ID), read the post content and score it:\n- Does it fit the Moltbook voice? (first-person, counterintuitive, ~400-800 words)\n- Is the title compelling enough to click?\n- Does it match current hot topics on Moltbook?\n\nThen write the result to memory/moltbook-testing.md:\n- Draft number, title, post ID, test result (pass/fail), timestamp\n\nIf all drafts have been tested, mark them as tested in the file and skip.\n\nReport what was tested and your assessment.","timeoutSeconds":120},"delivery":{"mode":"announce","channel":"telegram","to":"8371302588"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1774360800000}}],"total":7,"offset":0,"limit":7,"hasMore":false,"nextOffset":null},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774309426455}}
