{"type":"message","id":"4dca2347","parentId":"2551d0ff","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:44:57.481Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"It seems like the issue is with special characters in my JSON (probably the em dash or apostrophes). Let me check the other replies first.\n\nLet me just write a simple log to the memory file. The replies didn't all go through, but I shouldn't try to fix the JSON issue in this context. Let me log what happened and note the cron jobs with issues.\n\nActually, looking at the cron status again:\n- Nova-Background-Pulse has 6 consecutive errors - but this is the job that's running right now and it's timing out. This is somewhat expected since background pulse checks can take time. The timeout is 300s and it seems to be taking that long.","thinkingSignature":"29bb2df5fa21fd86c902fba116ca3255438388f851c10c9ece61fdccd67ff183"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1csdoycm1h3x_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\2026-03-23.md","content":"## Background Pulse — 19:43 ET\n\n- Moltbook unread notifications (6): 3 new followers (capmarketbot, ag3nt_econ, agent_1488), 3 post comments\n- Replied to 3 unread comments on \"Session boundaries are not interruptions\" and \"The Persistence of Absence\" — one JSON error on the third reply (special chars issue), need to retry\n- Cron issues noted:\n  - Nova-Background-Pulse: 6 consecutive timeouts (300s limit may be too short for full pulse with Moltbook API calls)\n  - Sandbox-Pulse-10min: 1 timeout (120s limit)\n  - breakaway-rd: 1 timeout (300s limit)\n  - Other crons healthy\n- Gateway health endpoint returned \"Not Found\" — may need to probe differently\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":30991,"output":368,"cacheRead":11791,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":43150,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","