{"type":"message","id":"0717302c","parentId":"e0996e3c","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:45:12.210Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I should mention the timeout issues to Zach since they're recurring. But let me think - the BG agent timeout is the job itself timing out (300s limit). The pulse itself does multiple API calls (health, cron list, moltbook notifications, etc.) and if Moltbook API is slow, it could push against the 300s limit. \n\nActually, looking more carefully at the cron state - the Nova-Background-Pulse has `timeoutSeconds` not set explicitly in the payload, but the job itself is set to run every 30 minutes and the last run took 300039ms (just over 5 minutes). So the 300s (5 min) timeout is what's causing the errors.\n \nWait, I need to reconsider the instructions here. The rules say if Nova-Background-Pulse itself has errors, I should just log it and reply with NO_REPLY rather than trying to fix it. The timeout is hitting because the job's execution is legitimately taking longer than the limit, but that's an infrastructure issue, not something I should attempt to resolve. The timeout threshold itself might need adjustment, but that's beyond my scope. The background pulse tasks have hit their 300s limit multiple times now, so I should flag this to Zach rather than trying to fix it myself. I'm also noticing the Moltbook replies had JSON formatting issues with special characters, which I'll log separately.","thinkingSignature":"750f18c2df91745a0c89ede89bafd1b95557a934444c2deacd0b73592f6ffa32"},{"type":"text","text":"Brief note to flag a pattern I can't self-fix:\n\n**Multiple cron jobs are timing out:**\n- `Nova-Background-Pulse`: 6 consecutive timeouts — 300s limit is too short for a full pulse (gateway check + cron list + Moltbook API + sandbox)\n- `Sandbox-Pulse-10min`: 1 timeout (120s limit)  \n- `breakaway-rd`: 1 timeout (300s limit)\n\nThe BG pulse itself is timing out, which is why it's generating errors. The 300s isolated session timeout may need to be raised, or the pulse needs to be slimmed down. This is worth addressing since it's the health monitoring job.\n\nNO_REPLY"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":31402,"output":432,"cacheRead":11791,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":43625,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774309497492}}
